entry.content:
For remote sources the  requestVideoFrameCallback  metadata should contain an captureTime metadata

https://wicg.github.io/video-rvfc/#dom-videoframecallbackmetadata-capturetime

Which is not present even when using the abs-capture-header extension, while the captureTimestamp is correctly populated (https://w3c.github.io/webrtc-extensions/#dom-rtcrtpcontributingsource-capturetimestamp)

Here is a js fiddle for the issue:
https://jsfiddle.net/6zsyqjge/9/

You can see that the output of the rvfc and the contribution sources:
```js
function vraf() {
	remoteVideo.requestVideoFrameCallback((now, metadata)=>{
    const receiver = pc2.getReceivers()[0];
    const csrc = receiver.getSynchronizationSources()[0];
  	console.log(now,metadata, csrc);
    vraf();
  });
}
```
